Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, when the words of the gods\Nresonated in the hearts of men…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.08,0:01:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two thousand years before\Nthe reign of the Chosen King...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.12,0:01:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the world had fallen into ruin due to\Nthe spread of monsters called daemons.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.20,0:01:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The nobles of House Caelum\Nused their god-given powers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.56,0:01:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to purge this scourge from the land,\Nearning the people's trust
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.29,0:01:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and spreading their influence\Nthroughout the realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.08,0:01:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Other lords voiced their support\Nfor House Caelum to lead the realm,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.62,0:02:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the gods, too, sought to select\Na ruler from among those men...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.87,0:02:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an absolute sovereign to sit atop\Nthe throne of the world's first kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.45,0:02:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were two candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.53,0:02:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One was ambitious,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.64,0:02:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a charismatic leader,\Nand the younger son of House Caelum:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.29,0:02:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somnus Lucis Caelum.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other was righteous,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.85,0:02:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somnus's older brother\Nwho dedicated his life to his people:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.79,0:02:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ardyn Lucis Caelum.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.04,0:02:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the Oracle,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.83,0:02:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a vessel for the voice of the gods,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.91,0:02:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I patiently awaited their decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.37,0:02:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you unwell, Lord Caelum?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.99,0:02:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tis nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, your dear brother did\Nunspeakable things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.28,0:03:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He rounded up those afflicted\Nby the Starscourge...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.87,0:03:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even those he merely suspected of infection,\Nand burned them all alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.16,0:03:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Caelum!\NPlease, you must save my daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.39,0:03:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.66,0:03:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Caelum?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.37,0:03:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- She's all better now.\N- Oh, thank the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.16,0:03:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- And thank YOU, milord!\N- Blessed be this day. It's a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.65,0:03:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Starscourge is a disease.\NWith the proper treatment, anyone can be spared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.02,0:03:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must not condemn our fellow man\Nand exile them as if they were monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.85,0:04:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even with your curative powers,\Nsurely you can't save everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.52,0:04:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we send the rest to the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.81,0:04:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey! You watch your tongue.\N- Why should I?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.86,0:04:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine if Somnus had\Nburned YOUR family alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.45,0:04:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you propose!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.06,0:04:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Such insolence!\N- There's nothing we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.29,0:04:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Caelum...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.06,0:04:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you are our one true king.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.11,0:04:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- He's right!\N- You're our only hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.13,0:04:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've no desire to sit the throne,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.44,0:04:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if it means the scourge would be purged\Nand that countless lives would be saved...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.73,0:04:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then I will gladly be your king.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.48,0:04:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't easy, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.41,0:04:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleeing the castle and coming \Nall the way here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.87,0:04:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A word of thanks is in order!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.06,0:04:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ineffably grateful, Aera.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.69,0:04:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I hope you, too, are grateful\Nfor those who so kindly escorted you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.65,0:04:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grateful for spending more time with me\Nthan a certain fiancé of mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.96,0:04:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.02,0:05:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.69,0:05:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place is incredible.\NHow old do you think these ruins are?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.41,0:05:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't the slightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.52,0:05:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither who made them, nor when nor why.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.98,0:05:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether they faded away on their own\Nor were erased from the annals of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.40,0:05:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their creator's name \Nremains a mystery to all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You needn't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if others forget your name...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.19,0:05:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will always remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- There he is!\N- Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.46,0:06:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- He's escaping!\N- After him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.30,0:06:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.63,0:06:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.82,0:06:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep looking!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.67,0:06:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By your leave, milord.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.21,0:06:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard the man: we lost him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.55,0:06:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And to think he and his betrothed could have\Nenjoyed a happy life free of conflict...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.21,0:06:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.13,0:06:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hour of the gods' decision is nigh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.59,0:07:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Lord Caelum!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.34,0:07:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ritual is already underway.\NNone must interfere!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.38,0:07:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hail, Oracle. What say the gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.17,0:07:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Crystal, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.90,0:07:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Crystal has no will of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.13,0:07:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Nothing, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you desire it, Somnus,\Nyou shall have my trust...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.50,0:07:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and their decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.64,0:07:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We feared the worst, milord!\NYou hadn't returned by dusk,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.05,0:07:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and with that torrential downpour...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.78,0:07:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your hospitality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.16,0:07:46.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Caelum!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.92,0:07:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, the word of the gods was heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.34,0:07:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ardyn Lucis Caelum,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.17,0:07:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you have been chosen to serve as king!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.88,0:07:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- At last!\N- Long live our king!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.92,0:07:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Praise be!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.96,0:08:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was me, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.00,0:08:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was me!\NI was chosen by the gods!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.92,0:08:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do forgive me for\Ndeceiving you all like this. However,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.22,0:08:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was necessary in order to lure\Nthe seditious traitor here today!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.21,0:08:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a miserable man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.76,0:08:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really covet my throne that badly?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.46,0:08:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.44,0:08:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gods have spoken,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.00,0:08:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I, Somnus Lucis Caelum, am king!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.37,0:08:50.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what if I object, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.49,0:08:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not take your life\Nso long as you renounce your na—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.86,0:09:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.61,0:09:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ardyn...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.93,0:09:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aera!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.01,0:09:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I'm going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.11,0:09:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Foolish woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.28,0:09:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.81,0:10:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I must fulfill my kingly calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.99,0:10:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What's happening!?\N- He's a monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's become the monster \NI made him out to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.94,0:10:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My people...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.28,0:10:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,must know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.32,0:10:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me... O gods above...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.49,0:10:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is... your True King?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.28,0:11:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that is your answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.49,0:11:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am unworthy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.53,0:11:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cursed to live as an immortal monster,\NArdyn was dubbed Adagium
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.74,0:11:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and imprisoned on the isle of Angelgard,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.24,0:11:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where his enmity for the royal family\Ngrew stronger with each passing year...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.90,0:11:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet in all accounts of Lucian history,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.02,0:11:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the name Ardyn Lucis Caelum is\Nnowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.57,0:12:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm waiting, Noct...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.01,0:12:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,